BARBERTON &#8211; Four suspects attempted to bomb an ATM machine at Jathira Fuel Station on the R40 in the early hours of this morning. According to Hi-Tech Barberton security official Rian Prinsloo, the three armed suspects got out of a silver Nissan Murano while the driver waited in the car.&#8220;One suspect was armed with what looked like an R5, and the other two had 9mm handguns on them.&#8221; The men held up the staff at gunpoint while they attempted to bomb the ATM machine which is situated in the shop.&#8220;They failed to open the ATM, so they robbed the till of over R4 000 cash and fled the scene.&#8221; The suspects were seen driving out towards Barberton.Read more here: Gang bosses obtaining insider information &nbsp;